            "text": ", Grams was so prominent in the car collector world that his bidder number with Mecum Auctions was no. 4! The Grams brothers got into cars at a young age when they started restoring old farm cars as teenagers, and the passion really hit high gear when they later sold one of their fixed up hot rods for $25,000. In recent years, Grams continued his desire of vehicle restoration and customization by creating \"whimsical curiosities\" from Model Ts including the Kodak camera car and circus car pictured below.",
